              "free_text": [
                " The experiment was performed at the",
                "Argonne Tandem Linac Accelerator System (ATLAS)",
                "facility using a 100Mo beam"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Active target was used. Multi-Sampling Ionization",
                "Chamber (MUSIC) detector was filled with a gas",
                "mixture of 95% He and 5% Kr. The purpose of the Kr",
                "was to increase the stopping power of the gas",
                "mixture. Two gas pressures were used. First at 498.1",
                "MeV 100Mo beam and a calibrated gas pressure of 408",
                "Torr, followed by a setting with a 474.8 MeV 100Mo",
                "beam and a calibrated gas pressure of 459 Torr."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "IOCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " MUlti-Sampling Ionization Chamber (MUSIC) was",
                "used to detect reaction products and beam",
                "particles.The segmented anode allows to measure",
                "position and energy loss of particles along their",
                "track, which allow discrimination between beam",
                "particles and reaction products."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Inverse kinematics was used."
              ]
            }
          ],
